<item>
            <title>[SOLR-15178] Non-existent dependency listed in solr-core</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15178</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Solr-core has a dependency, org.apache.solr:&lt;b&gt;server&lt;/b&gt;, which fails to download.&lt;br/&gt;
 For testing I created a test project here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/bszabo97/solr_master_dep_test&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/bszabo97/solr_master_dep_test&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 If I run the command &lt;tt&gt;gradle -q dependencies --configuration solrCore&lt;/tt&gt; the dependency org.apache.solr:server shows up and fails, though if I run &lt;tt&gt;gradle -q dependencies --configuration solrCore8&lt;/tt&gt; it doesn&apos;t show up at all.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
